Oberon was the consort of [[Titania]] and the father of [[Damh]], and presumably the father of [[Verenestra]] and the [[Prince of Frost]] as well. However, his relationship with Queen Titania was legendarily tempestuous: at times they were the dearest of lovers, at other times rivals, and at yet other times both. He was also the father of the archfey [[Selephra]],<ref>{{Cite dungeon/185/Court of Stars: The Bramble Queen|57}} and the archfey [[Hyrsam]] had been "born" from music he wrought long ago.<ref>{{Cite dragon/422/Hyrsam, Prince of Satyrs|4-6}}

With the rest of the Court, Oberon was allied with the [[Seldarine]], as well as various good deities of nature and hunting.

He was, like the rest of the Seelie Court, an enemy of the [[Goblinoid pantheon|goblinoid]] pantheon and the hag goddess [[Cegilune]], but most particularly the [[Queen of Air and Darkness]], whom he often urged Titania to war against.

He was also the leader of the faction of fey called the [[Green Fey]], which was primarily composed of wilder, more nature-oriented fey such as [[satyr]]s, [[dryad]]s, and [[treant]]s, as well as some [[elf|elves]] that dwelled in the Feywild. Other archfey of the Green Fey, such as Damh and Selephra, also answered to him.<ref>{{Cite dungeon/185/Court of Stars: The Bramble Queen|60}}
